textAnnotations.description:
But even his imagination, luckily for him,
did not visualise the awful truth - that
Mortyyd Owen was already qualifying for
the title of "First Woman to Enter Space."
"Where are we
going
Cadwallader when his child wind grasped
the fact that the
green earth was
failing
away
1
Mam?" inquired
inquired little
at a rate of knots.
